          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>
                                        <hi rend="underline">Hebrew</hi>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">
                                        <date>Adar 1842 (or 1847)</date>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">
                                        <placeName>Savannah</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Peace and every good to my honorable<lb/> friend
                                        etc. etc.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I want to announce to you, my dear and<lb/>
                                        honorable friend that I <del>have</del> received your
                                        letter<lb/> last <date>Friday</date>, and was exceedingly
                                        happy. You<lb/> may send the Pentateuchs in any way you
                                        like<lb/> if only they reach the two brothers whose
                                        name<lb/> I have already given you;
                                                  <persName><sic>Rebbi</sic> Nahum</persName><lb/>
                                        and <persName><sic>Rebbi</sic> Jacob Leib</persName> of the
                                        city of <placeName>Shliss–<lb/>shik</placeName> in
                                                  <placeName>Poland</placeName>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I very much regret the misfortune that<lb/> has
                                        befallen you, about which I read in the<lb/> Occident. But I
                                        know nothing with which<lb/> to comfort you. You know that
                                        it is of god.<lb/> As our sages said, "A man does not
                                        move<lb/> his finger etc....and who can say<lb/> to Him
                                        'What do you do?'", May God<lb/> free you from every evil,
                                        and may He fulfill<lb/> all his desires. Such is the wish of
                                        your<lb/> friend. Asher.....<persName role="author">Miles
                                                  hower</persName></p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">over</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>
                                        <hi rend="underline">The P.S. in Yiddish-German</hi>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">With regard to what you have written me<lb/> about
                                        your books, I spoke to <persName>Mr. Eckman</persName><lb/>
                                        He told me that he had sold some, and<lb/> that you will
                                        shortly hear from him.<lb/> You may send the Occident to
                                                  <persName>Taivel<lb/> Rosenbund</persName>. I
                                        shall continue to<lb/> use my best efforts in your
                                        service.</p>
                    </body>
